  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "By the time the compiler is able to enforce `view` and `pure` modifiers, it should be possible to detect expressions without side-effects.   This issue proposes a warning for expression statements without side-effects.\r\n\r\nFor instance, there would be a warning on the statement `3;`\r\n```\r\nWarning: a statement without side-effects.\r\nfunction f() { 3; }\r\n               ^^\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis should also catch the case of `var a = 0; a;`\r\n",
